{{Quote|We were engaged in a marathon Divoran holochess competition. You know the game, right? Each player controls fifteen holographic armies on a multi-level playing board, and the object is to capture all fifteen of the opponent's Emperor pieces.|Excerpt from "An Interview With Haaran Balmor, Jedi Master," from Madelein Aurin's ''Heroes Of The Republic''|<ref name="The Divoran Holochess Players">{{WEGCite|story=The Divoran Holochess Players|book=Galaxy Guide 9: Fragments from the Rim}}</ref>}}
'''Divoran holochess''' was a form of [[Holochess/Legends|holochess]] in which fifteen holographic armies were used by each two players on a multi-level board. The object was to capture all 15 of your opponent's [[Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] pieces.

